Ingredients
1.5L blueberries
110 mL cup brown sugar
230 mL balsamic vinegar
230 mL red wine vinegar
1 clove garlic, minced
1 onion, sliced
1 habanero pepper
1 dark beer
15mL tablespoon ground coriander
15mL tablespoon ground cumin
15mL tablespoon ground coffee
15mL tablespoon chipotle powder

Makes: ~6 8oz bottles 

Add all the ingredients for the sauce into a saucepan and cook for 2 hours over medium-low heat. 
Remove the sauce from the heat and place into a food processor or blender and puree. 
Strain the sauce and set aside.

Adapted from: http://www.foodnetwork.com/recipes/michael-symon/blueberry-bbq-recipe/index.html?oc=linkback

